Login to AWS Console
Create one S3 Bucket and give it an unique name like "host-website-project-<your name>"
Make sure ACLs, public access and bucket versioning are enabled.
Once the bucket is created, upload website content to you bucket.
Now to configure static website on S3 bucket, enable "Static website hosting"
There is a URL in the "Static website hosting" panel, under "Bucket website endpoint"
Here's what your Static website hosting panel should look like!
Now to make the objects in your S3 bucket public, use ACLs
Select the objects in your S3 bucket, and make them public using ACL.
Test the URL generated by S3 after enabling static website hosting
When you click on the URL generated for your static website, this is what you see:
